# CELEBRATE 70 — environment variables
#
# All VITE_-prefixed values are inlined into the client bundle at build
# time. They are visible to anyone who views the site. That is only safe
# if the backing resource is separately restricted:
#
#   - Google Maps API key → restrict by HTTP referrer in GCP Console
#     (allow your Vercel domain + localhost for dev).
#   - Supabase anon key    → the anon role is intended for the browser,
#     but all writes must be gated with Row Level Security policies.
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values. .env is gitignored.

VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your-google-maps-key-here

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Optional: fallback Maps key proxy used by Map.tsx when the direct key
# is absent. Leave unset unless you're running a Forge deployment.
# VITE_FRONTEND_FORGE_API_KEY=
# VITE_FRONTEND_FORGE_API_URL=
